name: valueSparse
equivalence.comment: Returns an instance's attribute value in internal format. Does exactly the same thing as value() if applied to an Instance.

name: numValues
equivalence.comment: Returns the number of values present. Always the same as numAttributes().

name: attributeSparse
equivalence.comment: Returns the attribute with the given index in the sparse representation. Same as attribute(int) for a DenseInstance.

name: valueSparse
equivalence.comment: Returns an instance's attribute value in internal format, given an index in the sparse representation. Same as value(int) for a DenseInstance.

name: add
equivalence.comment: Adds a value to the observed values It's equivalent to add(value, 1)

name: subtract
equivalence.comment: Removes a value to the observed values (no checking is done that the value being removed was actually added). It's equivalent to subtract(value, 1)
